ng","content":["mixed berries, to garnish"]}],"id":"r213378","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-KEnwGd7iM7g\/XZWdRyG-phI\/AAAAAAAAejw\/GpbXfV1QNMIcz6SWUsYRKn5ETIZYeIjegCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_E6eOwhLBYO6XTwGs.png","title":"Red, White and Blueberry Ice Cream Cake","publishedAt":"2017-06-23T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"22 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"37 g","calories":"1477 kJ \/ 353 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large freezable containers with lids (approx. 9 in. x 13 in.), springform pan (11 in.), fine mesh sieve, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["Place serving plate in freezer for 30 minutes before serving.","Leftover egg whites can be used for meringues.","Using a larger springform pan will give thinner layers. Make sure if using a smaller pan that you extend the height of pan by adding 2 inches of parchment to the inner edges for all three layers to fit.","Parchment paper: make sure to line sides of pan first then add a layer of parchment to the base of pan, covering up about ½ inch of the sides. Press parchment smooth before adding ice cream.","This recipe is best made three days in advance to allow ice cream to fully freeze before churning."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","48h","16 slices"]}